First Lady Melania Trump met with teens associated with the Truth Initiative to discuss the dangers of youth vaping. The Chief Marketing and Strategy Officer of Truth Initiative spoke about their mission to promote tobacco-free lives, and then the teenagers shared their experiences with vaping. The discussion revealed the health effects and addiction that come with vaping, as well as the ways in which these products are reaching underage youth. Melania Trump asked about access to the products and support for teens trying to quit. Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar and Senior Counselor Kellyanne Conway also participated in the listening session. Melania Trump praised the courage of the teenagers in sharing their stories and emphasized that vaping products should not be marketed to children. She commended schools and programs that educate students about the dangers of vaping.